{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"I'm a neuroscientist."},{"time":2000,"text":"And in neuroscience,"},{"time":4000,"text":"we have to deal with many difficult questions about the brain."},{"time":7000,"text":"But I want to start with the easiest question"},{"time":9000,"text":"and the question you really should have all asked yourselves at some point in your life,"},{"time":12000,"text":"because it's a fundamental question"},{"time":14000,"text":"if we want to understand brain function."},{"time":16000,"text":"And that is, why do we and other animals"},{"time":18000,"text":"have brains?"},{"time":20000,"text":"Not all species on our planet have brains,"},{"time":23000,"text":"so if we want to know what the brain is for,"},{"time":25000,"text":"let's think about why we evolved one."},{"time":27000,"text":"Now you may reason that we have one"},{"time":29000,"text":"to perceive the world or to think,"},{"time":31000,"text":"and that's completely wrong."},{"time":33000,"text":"If you think about this question for any length of time,"},{"time":36000,"text":"it's blindingly obvious why we have a brain."},{"time":38000,"text":"We have a brain for one reason and one reason only,"},{"time":41000,"text":"and that's to produce adaptable and complex movements."},{"time":44000,"text":"There is no other reason to have a brain."},{"time":46000,"text":"Think about it."},{"time":48000,"text":"Movement is the only way you have"},{"time":50000,"text":"of affecting the world around you."},{"time":52000,"text":"Now that's not quite true. There's one other way, and that's through sweating."},{"time":55000,"text":"But apart from that,"},{"time":57000,"text":"everything else goes through contractions of muscles."}]},{"cues":[{"time":59000,"text":"So think about communication --"},{"time":61000,"text":"speech, gestures, writing, sign language --"},{"time":64000,"text":"they're all mediated through contractions of your muscles."},{"time":67000,"text":"So it's really important to remember"},{"time":69000,"text":"that sensory, memory and cognitive processes are all important,"},{"time":73000,"text":"but they're only important"},{"time":75000,"text":"to either drive or suppress future movements."},{"time":77000,"text":"There can be no evolutionary advantage"},{"time":79000,"text":"to laying down memories of childhood"},{"time":81000,"text":"or perceiving the color of a rose"},{"time":83000,"text":"if it doesn't affect the way you're going to move later in life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":86000,"text":"Now for those who don't believe this argument,"},{"time":88000,"text":"we have trees and grass on our planet without the brain,"},{"time":90000,"text":"but the clinching evidence is this animal here --"},{"time":92000,"text":"the humble sea squirt."},{"time":94000,"text":"Rudimentary animal, has a nervous system,"},{"time":97000,"text":"swims around in the ocean in its juvenile life."},{"time":99000,"text":"And at some point of its life,"},{"time":101000,"text":"it implants on a rock."},{"time":103000,"text":"And the first thing it does in implanting on that rock, which it never leaves,"},{"time":106000,"text":"is to digest its own brain and nervous system"},{"time":109000,"text":"for food."},{"time":111000,"text":"So once you don't need to move,"},{"time":113000,"text":"you don't need the luxury of that brain."},{"time":116000,"text":"And this animal is often taken"},{"time":118000,"text":"as an analogy to what happens at universities"},{"time":120000,"text":"when professors get tenure,"},{"time":122000,"text":"but that's a different subject."}]},{"cues":[{"time":124000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":126000,"text":"So I am a movement chauvinist."},{"time":129000,"text":"I believe movement is the most important function of the brain --"},{"time":131000,"text":"don't let anyone tell you that it's not true."},{"time":133000,"text":"Now if movement is so important,"},{"time":135000,"text":"how well are we doing"},{"time":137000,"text":"understanding how the brain controls movement?"},{"time":139000,"text":"And the answer is we're doing extremely poorly; it's a very hard problem."},{"time":141000,"text":"But we can look at how well we're doing"},{"time":143000,"text":"by thinking about how well we're doing building machines"},{"time":145000,"text":"which can do what humans can do."}]},{"cues":[{"time":147000,"text":"Think about the game of chess."},{"time":149000,"text":"How well are we doing determining what piece to move where?"},{"time":152000,"text":"If you pit Garry Kasparov here, when he's not in jail,"},{"time":155000,"text":"against IBM's Deep Blue,"},{"time":157000,"text":"well the answer is IBM's Deep Blue will occasionally win."},{"time":160000,"text":"And I think if IBM's Deep Blue played anyone in this room, it would win every time."},{"time":163000,"text":"That problem is solved."},{"time":165000,"text":"What about the problem"},{"time":167000,"text":"of picking up a chess piece,"},{"time":169000,"text":"dexterously manipulating it and putting it back down on the board?"},{"time":172000,"text":"If you put a five year-old child's dexterity against the best robots of today,"},{"time":175000,"text":"the answer is simple:"},{"time":177000,"text":"the child wins easily."},{"time":179000,"text":"There's no competition at all."}]},{"cues":[{"time":181000,"text":"Now why is that top problem so easy"},{"time":183000,"text":"and the bottom problem so hard?"},{"time":185000,"text":"One reason is a very smart five year-old"},{"time":187000,"text":"could tell you the algorithm for that top problem --"},{"time":189000,"text":"look at all possible moves to the end of the game"},{"time":191000,"text":"and choose the one that makes you win."},{"time":193000,"text":"So it's a very simple algorithm."},{"time":195000,"text":"Now of course there are other moves,"},{"time":197000,"text":"but with vast computers we approximate"},{"time":199000,"text":"and come close to the optimal solution."},{"time":201000,"text":"When it comes to being dexterous,"},{"time":203000,"text":"it's not even clear what the algorithm is you have to solve to be dexterous."},{"time":205000,"text":"And we'll see you have to both perceive and act on the world,"},{"time":207000,"text":"which has a lot of problems."}]},{"cues":[{"time":209000,"text":"But let me show you cutting-edge robotics."},{"time":211000,"text":"Now a lot of robotics is very impressive,"},{"time":213000,"text":"but manipulation robotics is really just in the dark ages."},{"time":216000,"text":"So this is the end of a Ph.D. project"},{"time":218000,"text":"from one of the best robotics institutes."},{"time":220000,"text":"And the student has trained this robot"},{"time":222000,"text":"to pour this water into a glass."},{"time":224000,"text":"It's a hard problem because the water sloshes about, but it can do it."},{"time":227000,"text":"But it doesn't do it with anything like the agility of a human."},{"time":230000,"text":"Now if you want this robot to do a different task,"},{"time":233000,"text":"that's another three-year Ph.D. program."},{"time":236000,"text":"There is no generalization at all"},{"time":238000,"text":"from one task to another in robotics."}]},{"cues":[{"time":240000,"text":"Now we can compare this"},{"time":242000,"text":"to cutting-edge human performance."},{"time":244000,"text":"So what I'm going to show you is Emily Fox"},{"time":246000,"text":"winning the world record for cup stacking."},{"time":249000,"text":"Now the Americans in the audience will know all about cup stacking."},{"time":251000,"text":"It's a high school sport"},{"time":253000,"text":"where you have 12 cups you have to stack and unstack"},{"time":255000,"text":"against the clock in a prescribed order."},{"time":257000,"text":"And this is her getting the world record in real time."},{"time":264000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":272000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":277000,"text":"And she's pretty happy."},{"time":279000,"text":"We have no idea what is going on inside her brain when she does that,"},{"time":281000,"text":"and that's what we'd like to know."}]},{"cues":[{"time":283000,"text":"So in my group, what we try to do"},{"time":285000,"text":"is reverse engineer how humans control movement."},{"time":288000,"text":"And it sounds like an easy problem."},{"time":290000,"text":"You send a command down, it causes muscles to contract."},{"time":292000,"text":"Your arm or body moves,"},{"time":294000,"text":"and you get sensory feedback from vision, from skin, from muscles and so on."},{"time":297000,"text":"The trouble is"},{"time":299000,"text":"these signals are not the beautiful signals you want them to be."},{"time":301000,"text":"So one thing that makes controlling movement difficult"},{"time":303000,"text":"is, for example, sensory feedback is extremely noisy."},{"time":306000,"text":"Now by noise, I do not mean sound."},{"time":309000,"text":"We use it in the engineering and neuroscience sense"},{"time":311000,"text":"meaning a random noise corrupting a signal."},{"time":313000,"text":"So the old days before digital radio when you were tuning in your radio"},{"time":316000,"text":"and you heard \"crrcckkk\" on the station you wanted to hear,"},{"time":318000,"text":"that was the noise."},{"time":320000,"text":"But more generally, this noise is something that corrupts the signal."}]},{"cues":[{"time":323000,"text":"So for example, if you put your hand under a table"},{"time":325000,"text":"and try to localize it with your other hand,"},{"time":327000,"text":"you can be off by several centimeters"},{"time":329000,"text":"due to the noise in sensory feedback."},{"time":331000,"text":"Similarly, when you put motor output on movement output,"},{"time":333000,"text":"it's extremely noisy."},{"time":335000,"text":"Forget about trying to hit the bull's eye in darts,"},{"time":337000,"text":"just aim for the same spot over and over again."},{"time":339000,"text":"You have a huge spread due to movement variability."},{"time":342000,"text":"And more than that, the outside world, or task,"},{"time":344000,"text":"is both ambiguous and variable."},{"time":346000,"text":"The teapot could be full, it could be empty."},{"time":348000,"text":"It changes over time."},{"time":350000,"text":"So we work in a whole sensory movement task soup of noise."}]},{"cues":[{"time":354000,"text":"Now this noise is so great"},{"time":356000,"text":"that society places a huge premium"},{"time":358000,"text":"on those of us who can reduce the consequences of noise."},{"time":361000,"text":"So if you're lucky enough to be able to knock a small white ball"},{"time":364000,"text":"into a hole several hundred yards away using a long metal stick,"},{"time":367000,"text":"our society will be willing to reward you"},{"time":369000,"text":"with hundreds of millions of dollars."}]},{"cues":[{"time":372000,"text":"Now what I want to convince you of"},{"time":374000,"text":"is the brain also goes through a lot of effort"},{"time":376000,"text":"to reduce the negative consequences"},{"time":378000,"text":"of this sort of noise and variability."},{"time":380000,"text":"And to do that, I'm going to tell you about a framework"},{"time":382000,"text":"which is very popular in statistics and machine learning of the last 50 years"},{"time":385000,"text":"called Bayesian decision theory."},{"time":387000,"text":"And it's more recently a unifying way"},{"time":390000,"text":"to think about how the brain deals with uncertainty."},{"time":393000,"text":"And the fundamental idea is you want to make inferences and then take actions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":396000,"text":"So let's think about the inference."},{"time":398000,"text":"You want to generate beliefs about the world."},{"time":400000,"text":"So what are beliefs?"},{"time":402000,"text":"Beliefs could be: where are my arms in space?"},{"time":404000,"text":"Am I looking at a cat or a fox?"},{"time":406000,"text":"But we're going to represent beliefs with probabilities."},{"time":409000,"text":"So we're going to represent a belief"},{"time":411000,"text":"with a number between zero and one --"},{"time":413000,"text":"zero meaning I don't believe it at all, one means I'm absolutely certain."},{"time":416000,"text":"And numbers in between give you the gray levels of uncertainty."},{"time":419000,"text":"And the key idea to Bayesian inference"},{"time":421000,"text":"is you have two sources of information"},{"time":423000,"text":"from which to make your inference."},{"time":425000,"text":"You have data,"},{"time":427000,"text":"and data in neuroscience is sensory input."},{"time":429000,"text":"So I have sensory input, which I can take in to make beliefs."},{"time":432000,"text":"But there's another source of information, and that's effectively prior knowledge."},{"time":435000,"text":"You accumulate knowledge throughout your life in memories."},{"time":438000,"text":"And the point about Bayesian decision theory"},{"time":440000,"text":"is it gives you the mathematics"},{"time":442000,"text":"of the optimal way to combine"},{"time":444000,"text":"your prior knowledge with your sensory evidence"},{"time":446000,"text":"to generate new beliefs."}]},{"cues":[{"time":448000,"text":"And I've put the formula up there."},{"time":450000,"text":"I'm not going to explain what that formula is, but it's very beautiful."},{"time":452000,"text":"And it has real beauty and real explanatory power."},{"time":455000,"text":"And what it really says, and what you want to estimate,"},{"time":457000,"text":"is the probability of different beliefs"},{"time":459000,"text":"given your sensory input."},{"time":461000,"text":"So let me give you an intuitive example."},{"time":463000,"text":"Imagine you're learning to play tennis"},{"time":466000,"text":"and you want to decide where the ball is going to bounce"},{"time":468000,"text":"as it comes over the net towards you."},{"time":470000,"text":"There are two sources of information"},{"time":472000,"text":"Bayes' rule tells you."},{"time":474000,"text":"There's sensory evidence -- you can use visual information auditory information,"},{"time":477000,"text":"and that might tell you it's going to land in that red spot."},{"time":480000,"text":"But you know that your senses are not perfect,"},{"time":483000,"text":"and therefore there's some variability of where it's going to land"},{"time":485000,"text":"shown by that cloud of red,"},{"time":487000,"text":"representing numbers between 0.5 and maybe 0.1."}]},{"cues":[{"time":491000,"text":"That information is available in the current shot,"},{"time":493000,"text":"but there's another source of information"},{"time":495000,"text":"not available on the current shot,"},{"time":497000,"text":"but only available by repeated experience in the game of tennis,"},{"time":500000,"text":"and that's that the ball doesn't bounce"},{"time":502000,"text":"with equal probability over the court during the match."},{"time":504000,"text":"If you're playing against a very good opponent,"},{"time":506000,"text":"they may distribute it in that green area,"},{"time":508000,"text":"which is the prior distribution,"},{"time":510000,"text":"making it hard for you to return."},{"time":512000,"text":"Now both these sources of information carry important information."},{"time":514000,"text":"And what Bayes' rule says"},{"time":516000,"text":"is that I should multiply the numbers on the red by the numbers on the green"},{"time":519000,"text":"to get the numbers of the yellow, which have the ellipses,"},{"time":522000,"text":"and that's my belief."},{"time":524000,"text":"So it's the optimal way of combining information."}]},{"cues":[{"time":527000,"text":"Now I wouldn't tell you all this if it wasn't that a few years ago,"},{"time":529000,"text":"we showed this is exactly what people do"},{"time":531000,"text":"when they learn new movement skills."},{"time":533000,"text":"And what it means"},{"time":535000,"text":"is we really are Bayesian inference machines."},{"time":537000,"text":"As we go around, we learn about statistics of the world and lay that down,"},{"time":541000,"text":"but we also learn"},{"time":543000,"text":"about how noisy our own sensory apparatus is,"},{"time":545000,"text":"and then combine those"},{"time":547000,"text":"in a real Bayesian way."}]},{"cues":[{"time":549000,"text":"Now a key part to the Bayesian is this part of the formula."},{"time":552000,"text":"And what this part really says"},{"time":554000,"text":"is I have to predict the probability"},{"time":556000,"text":"of different sensory feedbacks"},{"time":558000,"text":"given my beliefs."},{"time":560000,"text":"So that really means I have to make predictions of the future."},{"time":563000,"text":"And I want to convince you the brain does make predictions"},{"time":565000,"text":"of the sensory feedback it's going to get."},{"time":567000,"text":"And moreover, it profoundly changes your perceptions"},{"time":569000,"text":"by what you do."},{"time":571000,"text":"And to do that, I'll tell you"},{"time":573000,"text":"about how the brain deals with sensory input."},{"time":575000,"text":"So you send a command out,"},{"time":578000,"text":"you get sensory feedback back,"},{"time":580000,"text":"and that transformation is governed"},{"time":582000,"text":"by the physics of your body and your sensory apparatus."}]},{"cues":[{"time":585000,"text":"But you can imagine looking inside the brain."},{"time":587000,"text":"And here's inside the brain."},{"time":589000,"text":"You might have a little predictor, a neural simulator,"},{"time":591000,"text":"of the physics of your body and your senses."},{"time":593000,"text":"So as you send a movement command down,"},{"time":595000,"text":"you tap a copy of that off"},{"time":597000,"text":"and run it into your neural simulator"},{"time":599000,"text":"to anticipate the sensory consequences of your actions."},{"time":603000,"text":"So as I shake this ketchup bottle,"},{"time":605000,"text":"I get some true sensory feedback as the function of time in the bottom row."},{"time":608000,"text":"And if I've got a good predictor, it predicts the same thing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":611000,"text":"Well why would I bother doing that?"},{"time":613000,"text":"I'm going to get the same feedback anyway."},{"time":615000,"text":"Well there's good reasons."},{"time":617000,"text":"Imagine, as I shake the ketchup bottle,"},{"time":619000,"text":"someone very kindly comes up to me and taps it on the back for me."},{"time":622000,"text":"Now I get an extra source of sensory information"},{"time":624000,"text":"due to that external act."},{"time":626000,"text":"So I get two sources."},{"time":628000,"text":"I get you tapping on it, and I get me shaking it,"},{"time":631000,"text":"but from my senses' point of view,"},{"time":633000,"text":"that is combined together into one source of information."}]},{"cues":[{"time":636000,"text":"Now there's good reason to believe"},{"time":638000,"text":"that you would want to be able to distinguish external events from internal events."},{"time":641000,"text":"Because external events are actually much more behaviorally relevant"},{"time":644000,"text":"than feeling everything that's going on inside my body."},{"time":647000,"text":"So one way to reconstruct that"},{"time":649000,"text":"is to compare the prediction --"},{"time":651000,"text":"which is only based on your movement commands --"},{"time":653000,"text":"with the reality."},{"time":655000,"text":"Any discrepancy should hopefully be external."},{"time":658000,"text":"So as I go around the world,"},{"time":660000,"text":"I'm making predictions of what I should get, subtracting them off."},{"time":663000,"text":"Everything left over is external to me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":665000,"text":"What evidence is there for this?"},{"time":667000,"text":"Well there's one very clear example"},{"time":669000,"text":"where a sensation generated by myself feels very different"},{"time":671000,"text":"then if generated by another person."},{"time":673000,"text":"And so we decided the most obvious place to start"},{"time":675000,"text":"was with tickling."},{"time":677000,"text":"It's been known for a long time, you can't tickle yourself"},{"time":679000,"text":"as well as other people can."},{"time":681000,"text":"But it hasn't really been shown, it's because you have a neural simulator,"},{"time":684000,"text":"simulating your own body"},{"time":686000,"text":"and subtracting off that sense."},{"time":688000,"text":"So we can bring the experiments of the 21st century"},{"time":691000,"text":"by applying robotic technologies to this problem."},{"time":694000,"text":"And in effect, what we have is some sort of stick in one hand attached to a robot,"},{"time":697000,"text":"and they're going to move that back and forward."},{"time":699000,"text":"And then we're going to track that with a computer"},{"time":701000,"text":"and use it to control another robot,"},{"time":703000,"text":"which is going to tickle their palm with another stick."},{"time":705000,"text":"And then we're going to ask them to rate a bunch of things"},{"time":707000,"text":"including ticklishness."}]},{"cues":[{"time":709000,"text":"I'll show you just one part of our study."},{"time":711000,"text":"And here I've taken away the robots,"},{"time":713000,"text":"but basically people move with their right arm sinusoidally back and forward."},{"time":716000,"text":"And we replay that to the other hand with a time delay."},{"time":719000,"text":"Either no time delay,"},{"time":721000,"text":"in which case light would just tickle your palm,"},{"time":723000,"text":"or with a time delay of two-tenths of three-tenths of a second."},{"time":727000,"text":"So the important point here"},{"time":729000,"text":"is the right hand always does the same things -- sinusoidal movement."},{"time":732000,"text":"The left hand always is the same and puts sinusoidal tickle."},{"time":735000,"text":"All we're playing with is a tempo causality."},{"time":737000,"text":"And as we go from naught to 0.1 second,"},{"time":739000,"text":"it becomes more ticklish."},{"time":741000,"text":"As you go from 0.1 to 0.2,"},{"time":743000,"text":"it becomes more ticklish at the end."},{"time":745000,"text":"And by 0.2 of a second,"},{"time":747000,"text":"it's equivalently ticklish"},{"time":749000,"text":"to the robot that just tickled you without you doing anything."},{"time":751000,"text":"So whatever is responsible for this cancellation"},{"time":753000,"text":"is extremely tightly coupled with tempo causality."},{"time":756000,"text":"And based on this illustration, we really convinced ourselves in the field"},{"time":759000,"text":"that the brain's making precise predictions"},{"time":761000,"text":"and subtracting them off from the sensations."}]},{"cues":[{"time":764000,"text":"Now I have to admit, these are the worst studies my lab has ever run."},{"time":767000,"text":"Because the tickle sensation on the palm comes and goes,"},{"time":769000,"text":"you need large numbers of subjects"},{"time":771000,"text":"with these stars making them significant."},{"time":773000,"text":"So we were looking for a much more objective way"},{"time":775000,"text":"to assess this phenomena."},{"time":777000,"text":"And in the intervening years I had two daughters."},{"time":779000,"text":"And one thing you notice about children in backseats of cars on long journeys,"},{"time":782000,"text":"they get into fights --"},{"time":784000,"text":"which started with one of them doing something to the other, the other retaliating."},{"time":787000,"text":"It quickly escalates."},{"time":789000,"text":"And children tend to get into fights which escalate in terms of force."},{"time":792000,"text":"Now when I screamed at my children to stop,"},{"time":794000,"text":"sometimes they would both say to me"},{"time":796000,"text":"the other person hit them harder."}]},{"cues":[{"time":799000,"text":"Now I happen to know my children don't lie,"},{"time":801000,"text":"so I thought, as a neuroscientist,"},{"time":803000,"text":"it was important how I could explain"},{"time":805000,"text":"how they were telling inconsistent truths."},{"time":807000,"text":"And we hypothesize based on the tickling study"},{"time":809000,"text":"that when one child hits another,"},{"time":811000,"text":"they generate the movement command."},{"time":813000,"text":"They predict the sensory consequences and subtract it off."},{"time":816000,"text":"So they actually think they've hit the person less hard than they have --"},{"time":818000,"text":"rather like the tickling."},{"time":820000,"text":"Whereas the passive recipient"},{"time":822000,"text":"doesn't make the prediction, feels the full blow."},{"time":824000,"text":"So if they retaliate with the same force,"},{"time":826000,"text":"the first person will think it's been escalated."}]},{"cues":[{"time":828000,"text":"So we decided to test this in the lab."},{"time":830000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":833000,"text":"Now we don't work with children, we don't work with hitting,"},{"time":835000,"text":"but the concept is identical."},{"time":837000,"text":"We bring in two adults. We tell them they're going to play a game."},{"time":840000,"text":"And so here's player one and player two sitting opposite to each other."},{"time":842000,"text":"And the game is very simple."},{"time":844000,"text":"We started with a motor"},{"time":846000,"text":"with a little lever, a little force transfuser."},{"time":848000,"text":"And we use this motor to apply force down to player one's fingers"},{"time":850000,"text":"for three seconds and then it stops."},{"time":853000,"text":"And that player's been told, remember the experience of that force"},{"time":856000,"text":"and use your other finger"},{"time":858000,"text":"to apply the same force"},{"time":860000,"text":"down to the other subject's finger through a force transfuser -- and they do that."},{"time":863000,"text":"And player two's been told, remember the experience of that force."},{"time":866000,"text":"Use your other hand to apply the force back down."},{"time":869000,"text":"And so they take it in turns"},{"time":871000,"text":"to apply the force they've just experienced back and forward."}]},{"cues":[{"time":873000,"text":"But critically,"},{"time":875000,"text":"they're briefed about the rules of the game in separate rooms."},{"time":878000,"text":"So they don't know the rules the other person's playing by."},{"time":880000,"text":"And what we've measured"},{"time":882000,"text":"is the force as a function of terms."},{"time":884000,"text":"And if we look at what we start with,"},{"time":886000,"text":"a quarter of a Newton there, a number of turns,"},{"time":888000,"text":"perfect would be that red line."},{"time":890000,"text":"And what we see in all pairs of subjects is this --"},{"time":893000,"text":"a 70 percent escalation in force"},{"time":895000,"text":"on each go."},{"time":897000,"text":"So it really suggests, when you're doing this --"},{"time":899000,"text":"based on this study and others we've done --"},{"time":901000,"text":"that the brain is canceling the sensory consequences"},{"time":903000,"text":"and underestimating the force it's producing."},{"time":905000,"text":"So it re-shows the brain makes predictions"},{"time":907000,"text":"and fundamentally changes the precepts."},{"time":910000,"text":"So we've made inferences, we've done predictions,"},{"time":913000,"text":"now we have to generate actions."},{"time":915000,"text":"And what Bayes' rule says is, given my beliefs,"},{"time":917000,"text":"the action should in some sense be optimal."}]},{"cues":[{"time":919000,"text":"But we've got a problem."},{"time":921000,"text":"Tasks are symbolic -- I want to drink, I want to dance --"},{"time":924000,"text":"but the movement system has to contract 600 muscles"},{"time":926000,"text":"in a particular sequence."},{"time":928000,"text":"And there's a big gap"},{"time":930000,"text":"between the task and the movement system."},{"time":932000,"text":"So it could be bridged in infinitely many different ways."},{"time":934000,"text":"So think about just a point to point movement."},{"time":936000,"text":"I could choose these two paths"},{"time":938000,"text":"out of an infinite number of paths."},{"time":940000,"text":"Having chosen a particular path,"},{"time":942000,"text":"I can hold my hand on that path"},{"time":944000,"text":"as infinitely many different joint configurations."},{"time":946000,"text":"And I can hold my arm in a particular joint configuration"},{"time":948000,"text":"either very stiff or very relaxed."},{"time":950000,"text":"So I have a huge amount of choice to make."},{"time":953000,"text":"Now it turns out, we are extremely stereotypical."},{"time":956000,"text":"We all move the same way pretty much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":959000,"text":"And so it turns out we're so stereotypical,"},{"time":961000,"text":"our brains have got dedicated neural circuitry"},{"time":963000,"text":"to decode this stereotyping."},{"time":965000,"text":"So if I take some dots"},{"time":967000,"text":"and set them in motion with biological motion,"},{"time":970000,"text":"your brain's circuitry would understand instantly what's going on."},{"time":973000,"text":"Now this is a bunch of dots moving."},{"time":975000,"text":"You will know what this person is doing,"},{"time":978000,"text":"whether happy, sad, old, young -- a huge amount of information."},{"time":981000,"text":"If these dots were cars going on a racing circuit,"},{"time":983000,"text":"you would have absolutely no idea what's going on."}]},{"cues":[{"time":986000,"text":"So why is it"},{"time":988000,"text":"that we move the particular ways we do?"},{"time":990000,"text":"Well let's think about what really happens."},{"time":992000,"text":"Maybe we don't all quite move the same way."},{"time":995000,"text":"Maybe there's variation in the population."},{"time":997000,"text":"And maybe those who move better than others"},{"time":999000,"text":"have got more chance of getting their children into the next generation."},{"time":1001000,"text":"So in evolutionary scales, movements get better."},{"time":1004000,"text":"And perhaps in life, movements get better through learning."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1007000,"text":"So what is it about a movement which is good or bad?"},{"time":1009000,"text":"Imagine I want to intercept this ball."},{"time":1011000,"text":"Here are two possible paths to that ball."},{"time":1014000,"text":"Well if I choose the left-hand path,"},{"time":1016000,"text":"I can work out the forces required"},{"time":1018000,"text":"in one of my muscles as a function of time."},{"time":1020000,"text":"But there's noise added to this."},{"time":1022000,"text":"So what I actually get, based on this lovely, smooth, desired force,"},{"time":1025000,"text":"is a very noisy version."},{"time":1027000,"text":"So if I pick the same command through many times,"},{"time":1030000,"text":"I will get a different noisy version each time, because noise changes each time."},{"time":1033000,"text":"So what I can show you here"},{"time":1035000,"text":"is how the variability of the movement will evolve"},{"time":1037000,"text":"if I choose that way."},{"time":1039000,"text":"If I choose a different way of moving -- on the right for example --"},{"time":1042000,"text":"then I'll have a different command, different noise,"},{"time":1044000,"text":"playing through a noisy system, very complicated."},{"time":1047000,"text":"All we can be sure of is the variability will be different."},{"time":1050000,"text":"If I move in this particular way,"},{"time":1052000,"text":"I end up with a smaller variability across many movements."},{"time":1055000,"text":"So if I have to choose between those two,"},{"time":1057000,"text":"I would choose the right one because it's less variable."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1059000,"text":"And the fundamental idea"},{"time":1061000,"text":"is you want to plan your movements"},{"time":1063000,"text":"so as to minimize the negative consequence of the noise."},{"time":1066000,"text":"And one intuition to get"},{"time":1068000,"text":"is actually the amount of noise or variability I show here"},{"time":1070000,"text":"gets bigger as the force gets bigger."},{"time":1072000,"text":"So you want to avoid big forces as one principle."},{"time":1075000,"text":"So we've shown that using this,"},{"time":1077000,"text":"we can explain a huge amount of data --"},{"time":1079000,"text":"that exactly people are going about their lives planning movements"},{"time":1082000,"text":"so as to minimize negative consequences of noise."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1085000,"text":"So I hope I've convinced you the brain is there"},{"time":1087000,"text":"and evolved to control movement."},{"time":1089000,"text":"And it's an intellectual challenge to understand how we do that."},{"time":1092000,"text":"But it's also relevant"},{"time":1094000,"text":"for disease and rehabilitation."},{"time":1096000,"text":"There are many diseases which effect movement."},{"time":1099000,"text":"And hopefully if we understand how we control movement,"},{"time":1101000,"text":"we can apply that to robotic technology."},{"time":1103000,"text":"And finally, I want to remind you,"},{"time":1105000,"text":"when you see animals do what look like very simple tasks,"},{"time":1107000,"text":"the actual complexity of what is going on inside their brain"},{"time":1109000,"text":"is really quite dramatic."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1111000,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1113000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1121000,"text":"Chris Anderson: Quick question for you, Dan."},{"time":1123000,"text":"So you're a movement -- (DW: Chauvinist.) -- chauvinist."},{"time":1127000,"text":"Does that mean that you think that the other things we think our brains are about --"},{"time":1130000,"text":"the dreaming, the yearning, the falling in love and all these things --"},{"time":1133000,"text":"are a kind of side show, an accident?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1136000,"text":"DW: No, no, actually I think they're all important"},{"time":1138000,"text":"to drive the right movement behavior to get reproduction in the end."},{"time":1141000,"text":"So I think people who study sensation or memory"},{"time":1144000,"text":"without realizing why you're laying down memories of childhood."},{"time":1146000,"text":"The fact that we forget most of our childhood, for example,"},{"time":1149000,"text":"is probably fine, because it doesn't effect our movements later in life."},{"time":1152000,"text":"You only need to store things which are really going to effect movement."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1155000,"text":"CA: So you think that people thinking about the brain, and consciousness generally,"},{"time":1158000,"text":"could get real insight"},{"time":1160000,"text":"by saying, where does movement play in this game?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1162000,"text":"DW: So people have found out for example"},{"time":1164000,"text":"that studying vision in the absence of realizing why you have vision"},{"time":1166000,"text":"is a mistake."},{"time":1168000,"text":"You have to study vision with the realization"},{"time":1170000,"text":"of how the movement system is going to use vision."},{"time":1172000,"text":"And it uses it very differently once you think about it that way."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1174000,"text":"CA: Well that was quite fascinating. Thank you very much indeed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1177000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}